{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Increase the success criteria for all future referendums to 60% of the vote",
        "additional_details": "Referendums can and have been deeply divisive, we therefore request a redefinition of the success criteria for future referendums to exceed the 50+1 rule to 60%.\r\n\r\nExamples of divisions created through the 50+1 rule would be the Scottish Independence referendum of 2014 and the \"Brexit\" referendum of 2016.",
        "background": "We request the Government create legislation requiring a majority of 60% in future referendums in order for the referendum results to be implemented.",
